title: Inner London ( UK ) : population 2011 , by ethnic group
summary: This bar chart has 6 columns on the x axis representing Ethnic Groups, and Share of population in each Ethnic Groups on the y axis.
The Share of population is highest at Ethnic Groups White and lowest at Ethnic Groups Gypsy/Traveller/Irish traveller.
The difference of Share of population between the highest and lowest Ethnic Groups is 57.2.

max_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Share of population for 6 number of Ethnic Groupss.
Ethnic Groups White has the highest Share of population and Gypsy/Traveller/Irish traveller has the lowest Share of population.
Second maximum Share of population is found at Ethnic Groups Black / African / Caribbean / Black British.
There is a difference of 57.2 between the maximum Ethnic Groups White and minimum Ethnic Groups Gypsy/Traveller/Irish traveller.

The Ethnic Groups White has the highest Share of population, followed by Black / African / Caribbean / Black British, and Asian / Asian British. Down to the Ethnic Groups Gypsy/Traveller/Irish traveller which is the lowest.
The highest value 57.3 at White is almost 3.43 times larger than the average value 16.72.
The Share of population is 100.3 if we add up values of all Ethnic Groupss.
